text:
Meet the Regulation Hotties Who Rescued 6 Teens Who Fell Through Ice on Central Park Pond 
No, really, they are models! The hotties, not the teens. NBC By Tess Koman Feb 21, 2017 Six teens fell through the ice covering the Central Park pond while trying to take a selfie Monday night, CBS New York reports. Two men skateboarding nearby saw the teens fall through and ran to help them — the boys, who were all 15 or 16 except for a 10-year-old in the bunch, were all rescued quickly enough they only suffered from mild hypothermia. All of them are expected to be released from the hospital today. Advertisement - Continue Reading Below According to the New York Daily News , Bennett Jonas, 23, and Ethan Turnbull, 24, both male models, tag-teamed the rescues — Jonas got in the water to pull the boys out and passed each one to Turnbull who dragged them to shore. While the first four boys were relatively easy to save, two more sunk deeper under the ice. A post shared by @bennett_jonas on Feb 20, 2017 at 8:39pm PST “I swam out and grabbed the last two guys and was able to get them to shore and keep them alive,” Jonas captioned the above Instagram reflecting on his experience. “I feel humbled and grateful that God called me to be there tonight, I’m still shaking and am completely shook by what I experienced,” Jonas added. “But I’m alive and so are 6 other kids who got very lucky tonight.” In his own Instagram post, Turnbull wrote he was in the “right place right time” to help and said he couldn’t have done it without Jonas’s help. A post shared by E T H A N. T. ™ (@ethanturnbull) on Feb 20, 2017 at 8:47pm PST Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Meanwhile, the FDNY cautioned New Yorkers not to attempt anything similar and tweeted a picture of the ice the boys cracked through. NYers, there is no such thing as safe ice. Learn to be #FDNYSmart at https://t.co/zii5uY5RoV pic.twitter.com/FLQ3K5e0Xy — FDNY (@FDNY) February 21, 2017 Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Also, Jonas looks like Ashton Kutcher. Turnbull doesn’t look like anyone famous, but he’s from Australia and also very good-looking. Don't let anyone tell you there isn't any good left in this world. God bless. All best.
